## 🎓 PRO-LEVEL: Design Patterns Used

| Pattern | Where | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **Strategy/Dispatcher** | [ShopeeWebhookProcessor](file:///d:/Inventrik%202.0/Project%201/Shopee/src/main/java/com/inventrik/integration/shopee/service/ShopeeWebhookProcessor.java#26-137) | Routes events without hard-coupling to specific handlers |
| **Template Method** | [executeWithRetry()](file:///d:/Inventrik%202.0/Project%201/Shopee/src/main/java/com/inventrik/integration/shopee/service/ShopeeServiceImpl.java#154-206) | Same algorithm (auth→call→retry) for every API, only details change |
| **Facade** | [ShopeeService](file:///d:/Inventrik%202.0/Project%201/Shopee/src/main/java/com/inventrik/integration/shopee/service/ShopeeService.java#19-53) interface | Hides complexity behind a simple interface |
| **Singleton (via Spring)** | All `@Service`, `@Component` | One instance per bean, managed by Spring container |
| **Cache-Aside** | [TokenCacheManager](file:///d:/Inventrik%202.0/Project%201/Shopee/src/main/java/com/inventrik/integration/shopee/auth/TokenCacheManager.java#19-79) | Check cache first, fetch on miss, invalidate on error |
| **Separation of Concerns** | Layered architecture | Each layer has one responsibility |

### Designed for Future AOP

The retry, auth, and logging logic is currently inline but structured so you can later write:
```java
@Around("execution(* com.inventrik..ShopeeServiceImpl.*(..))")
public Object retryOnUnauthorized(ProceedingJoinPoint joinPoint) {
    // Aspect handles retry automatically
}
```
This would remove retry logic from [ShopeeServiceImpl](file:///d:/Inventrik%202.0/Project%201/Shopee/src/main/java/com/inventrik/integration/shopee/service/ShopeeServiceImpl.java#45-249) entirely — zero code changes to the service itself.

---

## 🔄 Request Flow Summary

### Webhook Flow (Shopee → You)
```
Shopee sends POST /ims/shopee/events.json
    → ShopeeWebhookController receives it
        → ShopeeWebhookProcessor.process() dispatches by event type
            → handleOrderEvent() / handlePaymentEvent() / etc.
                → Logs the event (no business logic — that's the main system's job)
    ← Returns 200 OK to Shopee
```

### API Call Flow (You → Shopee)
```
Your code calls shopeeService.getOrderDetails(request)
    → ShopeeServiceImpl.executeWithRetry()
        → TokenCacheManager.getValidToken() — check cache
            → If expired: ShopeeAuthService.refreshAccessToken()
        → ShopeeSignatureUtil.generateSignShop() — sign the request
        → RestTemplate.exchange() — HTTP call to Shopee
            → If 401: clear token → refresh → retry ONCE
        → Return deserialized response
```

---

## 📋 What This Project DOES NOT Do (By Design)

| Not Included | Why |
|---|---|
| Database | This is a communication layer, not a data store |
| Business logic | The main system decides what to DO with the data |
| Frontend | No UI needed — it's a backend SDK |
| Real credentials | Security — use env vars in production |
| API-key auth | Shopee uses OAuth, not static API keys |
